data.title: Calendar — Rockwood Music Hall NYC
data.text:
Spaghetti Eastern

spotify

Spaghetti Eastern Electro Dub is the genre-leaping project led by NYC & Hudson Valley-based guitarist/keyboardist Sal Cataldi. Like his solo project Spaghetti Eastern Music, the Spaghetti Eastern Electro Dub spin-off marries acid jazz-guitar-driven instrumentals and improvs with ambient soundscapes that are peppered with elements of Jamaican dub, funk, progressive rock and free jazz. Cataldi is abetted in the project by bassist Tom “Spontaneous” Semioli, drummers Dirk Drazen and Dave Donen and an Eastern music master, dilbura player/sitarist Dawoud “The Sufi Renegade” Kringle. Cataldi debuted Spaghetti Eastern with the critically-acclaimed 2016 album, “Sketches of Spam,” which has been followed with a number of EPs and singles. The New York Times says Cataldi “has a beat unmistakably his own” while Time Out New York praises his "delicate guitar work and the hauntingly moody atmosphere he conjures.” Called “beautiful and unique” by WFUV’s Mixed Bag and “charmingly melodic and off-center” by WFMU. Hudson Valley One has called Spaghetti Eastern “part Sergio Leone fever dream, part Ravi Shankar raga, a whirling dervish of musical creation.” Chronogram Magazine called his recent release, the exploratory solo guitar score for the dance piece 2x2x4, “cool, melodic, inspired and transcendent, a wave of sonic warmth and light.” Psychedelic Baby Magazine calls it “the perfect sonic tonic for these troubled times.” Cataldi is also a member of the ambient guitar duo Guitars A Go Go, the poetry/music project Vapor Vespers and the psych/surf quartet, Spaceheater. Look for his music at www://spaghettieasternmusic.bandcamp.com

View Event →

Val Kinzler

website

Recent participant in Lincoln Center’s Anthem To Us project, Martin Guitars Women In Music Scholarship recipient and top finalist in the John Lennon Songwriting contest,Val’s musical catalog of original songs and collaborations with top artists is nothing short of A list.

In listening to her lineage of music, you will hear Val’s theatrical edge which she has used to create her own soulful sound incorporating rock, rhythm and blues. Val shares a lifetime of joy, pain, love, and loss in her lyrics. Her emotional music has been embraced across her fans, fellow musicians, the music industry, and the women in music she touches daily in her NYC Women Who Rock online community.

Val Is currently signed to Aurally Records

View Event →

The Patti Rothberg Band

Patti Rothberg's music career started with New York City subway busking. Her 1996 EMI debut gold album, "Between the One and the Nine", led to appearances on Jay Leno, David Letterman, international TV, and major world touring, opening for artists such as Pat Benatar, Chris Isaak, Paul Westerberg, The B52's, and many others. She also performed at NYC radio station Z100's "Girls Rule the Yule" at Madison Square Garden in 1996.

She has released nine albums, had a number one hit on rock radio, and a top 25 single on the US billboard charts with the song "Inside". Patti's music has had a significant influence on generation X rock fans, especially women.

Other band members; Mick "Crash" Oakleaf (The Nothing, Disturbed Furniture, and too many others to list) on drums and backing vocals. He is also a NYC recording studio audio veteran (Unique, Howard Schwartz, Sony, Kampo Studios).

Matt DeSilva, is on bass and backing vocals (Toast, Custard Wally). He was Manager of the Guitar Department at Manny's Music on 48th street's music row in NYC and used to write for Bass Player magazine.

View Event →

Ryan Luce

instagram

“We often talk about how we would have found each other in any life.” Since the release of Ryan Luce’s debut album Country House, a lot has changed for him and his surroundings. “I got engaged, moved, and married in the year after my last record.” As Luce and his wife settled into their new surroundings it inspired him to write his new single Gemini about starting their lives together as a wedding present to her. “This song captures a chapter of my life that I'd like to remember when I get old. Most people don’t get that chance to capture it and store it in a bottle. This song is more than a song, it’s a photograph to me.” Taking a different path from his last record that was filled with fictional characters, writing about his life came as a challenge leaving Luce to contemplate what it means to share the rest of your life with someone. “When the unwritten road is yours it’s not about plot points but on feelings like faith and looking back on all the little things that had to go your way. It makes you humble.” Throughout Gemini Luce paints a picture of the neighborhood and the life he leads: “Every Sunday we go to our grocery store that plays old Italian songs over the PA and my wife says it was placed there by her grandfather for us.” After writing Gemini, Luce recruited singer-songwriter Sam Weber to produce. “I felt Gemini was my song but a kindred spirit to what I heard Sam was doing. I listened to his records the last couple years and loved his Easy Street EP, that convinced me to reach out.” Mastered by Justin Perkins from Mystery Room Mastering and mixed by Sean Sullivan (Molly Tuttle, Tyler Childers) the 3 of them crafted a dynamic sound to wrap around Luce’s voice. “ I feel my voice on Gemini is strong yet gentle. I had to keep it hidden from my wife for a long time and somehow that helped when I really had to sing it for her.” Gemini is a song that is awash in textures and sounds that add a new palette to Luce’s songs while keeping his songwriting grounded in our brief moments of joy. “Passages in our life are so brief, writing this song was the only way to keep it.”

View Event →

Will Phelps

instagram | website

Will Phelps is a multidisciplinary artist based in Brooklyn. His debut album "Isn't It All Wonderfull Now?" is slated to be released in 2024.

View Event →

Jamie Thomas

instagram

Jamie Thomas had his musical epiphany not at the proverbial crossroads but a schoolyard in Astoria, Queens, where the music of Bob Dylan, Johnny Cash, The Rolling Stones and others touched his soul and inspired him to write songs. He honed his skills as a performer playing New York clubs with his band 3rd Man Out before striking out on his own, making his bones as a solo act in the ground zero of the American folk movement, Greenwich Village's the Bitter End. He later headed south of Mason-Dixon line spending time in Nashville before landing in Austin, TX in 2003. While in Austin Jamie shared the stage with Texas music legends Bill Carter (writer of Crossfire for SRV) and Charlie Sexton (Bob Dylan, Elvis Costello). In 2012 Jamie headed west to Los Angeles for a year of writing and gigging at the Viper Room, the Mint, and the House of Blues. Jamie continues to perform his own steeped-in-the-tradition originals with his reinterpretations of other numbers from the great real American music songbook that span from its origins to today.

View Event →

Apollo Flowerchild

linktr.ee

Apollo Flowerchild is an NYC-based singer-songwriter multi-instrumentalist who isn’t married to any single genre. Since starting their musical journey 8 years ago they have managed to sing on Broadway, be recognized by billboard among other publications, and perform all across NYC music venues including but not limited to The Mercury Lounge, Heaven can wait, Rockwood Music hall, 3 Dollar Bill and Purgatory. Apollos voice Carries a sense of soulful light and beauty and is pushed even further by thoughtful, earnest and wacky lyricism. Apollo believes "genre is simply a storytelling tool to help easily characterize the atmosphere of a song but what happens if no single genre satisfies you? you experiment! you alchemize musical motifs and textures to do the job you want it to." there has been no shortage of exploration with their debut Album Drawing 101 introducing Apollos tastes for fun New Orleans brass with "I THINK I KNOW?" the tender simplicity of singer-songwriter folk with "A Delicate Reminder" and the their unique storytelling style glazed over glorious samba/ Bossa nova sounds in "Palavras No Osso".

View Event →

Carolann Solebello

website | youtube | instagram

CAROLANN SOLEBELLO is a performing songwriter born and bred in NYC. Her smooth, compelling voice and warm acoustic guitar style nod to rural folk traditions while her rhythmic precision and sophisticated phrasing plant her firmly in the urban present. Carolann has recorded five solo albums, six band albums, hosted open mics, curated songwriter series, and won a bunch of songwriting awards.

View Event →

Ida Metsberg

Finland is known for being one of the happiest places in the world and a place of clean, pure, natural beauty. It's no surprise that Ida Metsberg, native to the land, brings deep, meaningful, vibrant, and nourishing energy through her songs. Now calling New York her home, the singer/songwriter has been bringing her light and unique perspective to the city streets and leaving people with a memorable, and lasting impression.

With nods to artists like Sara Bareilles and Anna Nalick, Ida blends Pop and Folk with intelligent, thoughtful structure and lyrics. Even songs that are more solemn and serious in tone leave you feeling hopeful and introspective. Her craft is her therapy and expression of her deepest self. Ida writes for her own healing and at times to speak her piece to people that have hurt her. This style of genuine rawness and passion resonates with anyone who has loved, lost, and can still celebrate life and look inside, honestly.

Ida is notable for playing shows across New York City, as well as all over the US, and with her theater background, her show is a must-watch. Her debut EP, Somebody New, was released in 2022, and she is currently recording new music, to be released later this year. Ida was nominated Performer of the Year in 2023 by Finlandia Foundation National.

View Event →

Ellie Grace

website | spotify | instagram

Born and raised in Nashville, Tennessee, Ellie Grace uplifts the classic roots of Nashville folk and bluegrass, while adding her own dream-like vocal sounds and soul rhythms. As the sole writer of all her songs, Ellie's identity as an artist is clearly one with her identity as a person. Her authentic, wrenching, and imaginative lyrics display her being without filter. Ellie's debut album Wings and new singles, are a collection of stories intended for the listener to feel full at heart and transformed in spirit. Her style is the communion of country storytelling, with indie/folk foundations, and a dash of contemporary R&B. This unique blend of genres gives this singer/songwriter the ability to convey the collective experiences of human beings.

View Event →

Sam Woolf

spotify | instagram | website

SAM WOOLF is a highly collaborative singer-songwriter known for his original compositions and pitch perfect vocals. Sam gained national recognition as a finalist on American Idol where he placed in the Top 5. Sam has been hailed as a "natural singer whose soul and passion are undeniable in every note he sings." His performances and recordings have obtained millions of views and Sam receives tremendous support from his fan club, the "WOOLFPACK," on social media.

View Event →

Annabel Asher

instagram | website

Annabel Asher is a singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and whatever she feels like doing-ist, hailing from Los Angeles and residing in Brooklyn. Asher’s musical universe is hedonistic, blunt, mystical, eclectic, and full of contradictions. Exploring the parallel terrain of euphoria and tragedy, their musical expression in the certain power of giving into your true feelings. Ranging a full spectrum of genre and emotion, Asher’s trademark style is not one style at all, but a chameleonic ability to shapeshift. What unites their discography is a singular intensity, conveyed via their soul-bearing alto gravel and grimy bass-laden production. Their next single, SHUT ME UP, is out August 2nd, and their debut EP, BESTSELLER, comes out Fall 2024.

View Event →

No Love Songs

NO LOVE SONGS is a SOUTH BROOKLYN GRUNGE TRIO. RYAN BAZINET leads the band on guitar and vocals, with GUSTAVO MARRON on drums and ERNESTO "LUI" RODRIGUEZ on bass. Their heavy sound makes them equally at home in the environs of punk, hardcore, metal, or straight up rock. In 2024 they founded FRIENDS & ALIENS RECORDS.

View Event →

Sama Thakore

linktr.ee | spotify | instagram

Sama Thakore is a multifaceted artist, excels as a singer-songwriter, music producer, mix engineer and a captivating performer. A graduate of Berklee college of music (NYC), she masterfully blends Hindustani (Indian) Classical Vocals and Western Vocals, infusing her music with rich cultural depth. Splitting her time between the vibrant music scenes of Mumbai and NYC, she draws inspiration from diverse landscapes. Her latest creations, meticulously crafted at the iconic Power Station at Berklee NYC, showcases her remarkable talents in writing, recording, singing, producing and mixing. Rooted in her Hindustani heritage, Sama has inherited her musical prowess from her mother, forging a deeply personal connection to her craft that resonates in every note she shares. She has created a very unique sonic experience that leaves an indelible mark on the soul.

View Event →

Schimon Dieseler

Schimon Dieseler is an independent, Washington-based rock musician with a distinctive blend of raw authenticity and introspective lyricism. Establishing the term “Melancholy-as-a-Service”, he crafts music that resonates with many young professionals who experience the tension between their true passion and the day job.

View Event →

Alana Silver

instagram

Alana Silver is a singer and songwriter living in San Francisco! She and her guitarist, Mac McCann, met last year and formed a 5-piece band, Tomboy. They have a shared love for the energy of blues rock revival and the more reflective melodies of indie and folk. With over 15 original songs, they love performing their music alongside crowd-pleaser covers. They can't wait to perform at Rockwood!

View Event →

STRAWBERRY JAM

Instagram

Strawberry Jam is an improvised open jam hosted by Jazz Fusion band Strawberry Sun. The jam is open to all vocalists, guitarists, bassists, keyboardists, drummers, etc, just bring your own instrument! The jam will focus heavily on improvised grooves, and combine elements of jazz, funk, rock, hip hop and R&B,

View Event →

Dave Achelis and 8ACE

website

Dave Achelis and 8ACE Dave was born in NYC a long time ago. Hearing “Louie Louie” by the Kingsmen in 1963 changed his life forever. Already adequate on the guitar from playing along with his sister’s folk music collection, and propelled by The Beatles a year later, he has played in bands ever since. The early 70s found him on radio stations as a disc jockey, and he later found work as an engineer/producer recording an array of artists, such as The New York Dolls, Binky Phillips and The Planets, Elliot Murphy, Jon Paris, Stu Daye, and perhaps most famously, The Misfits. Coincidently, he also was lucky enough to work with Jazz Greats like Dave Brubeck, Paul Desmond ,Sonny Rollins, Dexter Gordon, Duke Jordan and many others! He has also played guitar with almost everybody in the city at one time or another, highlights being Larry Estridge and Nightwatch, The Law, Mr Lucky, The Cash Cows, and his present day band, 8 ACE, featuring Roger Murdock on drums, Amy Madden on bass, and Zonder Kennedy on guitar. Not finding the type of music he likes on radio, the internet, or on TV, he took it upon himself to write and record his first solo CD, with the help of 8 ACE. He hopes kids as well as adults will find music that might drift in tempo, or vocals that aren’t auto-tuned, will remind them of the excitement rock music should be providing.

View Event →

Caleb Moore

spotify | instagram

Caleb Moore is a 26-year-old artist, songwriter, and producer from New York City. A multi-instrumentalist and film composer, Caleb does much of his songwriting and production solo - his music inhabits a groove focused, alternative-R&B space while his vocals and lyrics contrast in their vulnerability and sincerity. He cites artists including Tyler the Creator, James Blake, Rex Orange County, Lauryn Hill and Gustavo Santaolalla as inspirations, but this group only slightly hints at the scope of Caleb’s musical range. His palate is as organic and raw as it is contemporary and rhythmic. And despite his strong emphasis on the musical backdrop, what may come through most is his vocal honesty and insatiable desire for a good hook.

View Event →

deTournai

website | instagram | youtube

deTournai, DC's "progressive rock brother duo" and “brotherly prog-rock duo” as described by The Washington Post and Washingtonian Magazine, and native to the Washington, DC area, has played several acclaimed shows in the DC area and NYC since their forming in Summer of 2021, including Jammin’ Java, the National Cherry Blossom Festival, Rockwood Music Hall, Pete’s Candy Store, The Exchange Saloon and Superfine Art Fair, and regular shows in the summers at The Corolla Beer Garden in Corolla, NC. Bandmates and brothers Vasilis and Christos, born and raised in the Washington, DC area, are formally trained in classical piano since age five. A mix of progressive and indie rock, deTournai brings a fresh sound with classical roots. Their debut single, Adore You, written and produced by the artists, combines elements of rock and pop, infused with passionate guitar solos and fills, leaving the listener both relaxed and engaged in vocals and guitar.

View Event →

Aiden James

Website | Instagram | Youtube | Spotify | Apple Music

Aiden James is a captivating singer songwriter hailing from Philadelphia. His voice is reminiscent of Matt Nathanson, David Gray and Phil Collins. As on MTV Logo & Vh1 he's self-taught musician. Aiden consistently demonstrates his commitment to honing his craft & pushing creative boundaries. Seeing AJ live is a charming, inspiring & authentic revelation in modern culture. Through his music, he connects with audiences on a deep & personal level, providing solace and relatability through shared experiences. RSVP now!

View Event →

Elaine Rojas

linktr.ee

The granddaughter of a jazz musician, Elaine grew up in a household filled with music. At the age of four she began to write poetry which would later serve as the foundation to her songwriting. Elaine’s original music is a fusion of her jazz roots and more recent immersion into R&B and alternative genres of music. Some of her earliest influences range from Ella Fitzgerald to John Mayer and more recently include artists such as Matt Corby and Faye Webster.

View Event →

Luther Black and the Cold Hard Facts

Spotify | instagram | Facebook | Website

Luther Black and the Cold Hard Facts take listeners along on a soul-searching journey told through the songs of a road-worn traveler who has experienced life’s ups and downs and lived to tell the tale. Singer-songwriter-producer Rick Wagner's tunes come straight from the heart with a nod towards Outlaw Country’s founders Willie, Waylon, Johnny and Kris, delivered in a deep, raspy voice that American Songwriter says “hits with a cool sincerity that is a genuine rarity in the modern musical landscape.”

The 2020 debut album won critical acclaim for its “great stories about wisdom gained from hardscrabble living, similar to Ray Wylie Hubbard, Guy Clark and Townes Van Zandt” (Americana Music Show). The 2022 follow-up Moment Of Truth is a tasteful blend of rock, folk, country and blues with a cinematic undercurrent, bringing to mind Ry Cooder or later day Bob Dylan. Among the album's 12 tracks is a hypnotic cover of Dylan's , hailed by Rolling Stone as a "Song You Need To Know." Their 3rd album released in April, 2024 continues the tradition of well-crafted, heartfelt songs with a Dark Americana cadence that lands somewhere between Nick Cave and Johnny Cash."Classic, compelling songwriting that stirs the soul. Rick Wagner delivers a gritty vocal, full of earthy character and the overall impact is in the vein of Cash’s American Recordings period." says AmericanaUK.

View Event →

Arco

spotify | instagram | website

Antonio Arco, going by the stage name ARCO, is a Spanish singer, guitarist, composer, writer and lyricist, previously known for leading the Andalusian band El Puchero del Hortelano until late 2015. With them he toured Latin America and Europe until early 2016 when he began his solo career. Since then, he has released four albums, two of them for Warner Music and two with Altafonte, which have entered the best-seller list reaching the 8th position with his debut and have been selected by various media such as Mondo Sonoro or Rock Sesión as albums of the year when they were released. He has toured Spain, selling out many dates, and has also given concerts in Latin America and the USA, and has also starred in the documentary film “Octavas” with Spanish artist Jorge Drexler and Brazilian musician Seu Jorge, a film that has been selected for several international festivals and has accumulated an average score of 7.8 on the prestigious independent film channel Filmin. At Rockwood, Arco brings an acoustic show with piano and guitar where the audience will be able to enjoy his particular fusion between rock and Spanish flamenco folk. All a hatching of creativity that continues to make him one of the main referents of the Andalusian rock and flamenco fusion scene, but above all, undeniable proof of the authenticity and quality of his lyrics.

View Event →

Ted Sablay

website | instagram

Guitarist and musical director of The Killers touring band Ted Sablay continues his successful music career as a new solo artist.

Appealing to fans of indie, alternative and classic rock, Sablay’s music features strong guitar work and relatable, emotionally resonant lyrics, often exploring themes of love, longing, and life's ups and downs. With a relaxed and natural vocal delivery that complements the music's accessible and down-to-earth feel, Sablay captures the spirit of earlier rock eras while still sounding fresh and relevant.

After opening for Chris Isaak and the Wallflowers and completing a summer UK tour, Sablay returns to the Rockwood Music Hall September 13th to play new material from his upcoming album.

View Event →

Mary Edwards

instagram | bandcamp

Mary Edwards is a composer, songwriter and sound artist whose projects range from recordings and performances "evocative of epic film soundtracks combined with lyrical intimacy..." (Time Out NY), to cinematic audio and immersive environmental/architectural sound installations. Themes of temporality, impermanence and the natural world are interspersed throughout her work.

View Event →

Arissa Claire Brown

spotify | instagram

Arissa is a singer-songwriter combining folk roots, indie pop/rock, and queer narratives. Their debut EP, ‘Choking on Closeness,’ will be released in October later this year! In her free time, Arissa can be found frolicking, reading, and searching for band members.

View Event →

Eli Waltz

Spotify | Instagram | YouTube | TikTok | Facebook | Website

Eli Waltz is a world traveler and American folk musician who focuses the sum of his experiences on the road into a sound reminiscent of a different time. His music draws from the musical traditions of American Blues, Folk, “rock ‘n’ roll” and Chinese guqin music; his lyrics are inspired by the poets of the Beat Generation. He is heralded for his philosophical lyricism, unconventional chord progressions and hard-hitting harmonica solos. He weaves in traditional Chinese music–inspired by months and years living in Beijing and Yunnan as a working musician–and even classical music to create a signature folk sound. He has earned comparisons to musicians ranging from Ray Lamontagne to Colter Wall to Gregory Alan Isakov, and he aims to build upon and honor the legacies of his all-time favorites: Townes Van Zandt, John Lee Hooker, John Fahey and Bob Dylan. Waltz has shared the stage with nationally-recognized artists including Willie Carlise, Andrew Combs and Rett Madison and his music has received praise from Sir Paul McCartney among other musical heroes. He is part of a new wave of up-and-coming American Blues and Folk artists.

View Event →

Taylor Abrahamse / Jill Matundan

facebook | instagram | youtube | website

Like a maple leaf in a gust above the Ontario prairies, Taylor Abrahamse blissfully floats between the borders of song, genre & gender with his/her deftly crafted, hook-laden hammerclaw pop. A Paul Simon/Jim Carrey crossbreed & Kerrville Newfolk Winner, he’ll leave you laughing, inspired, and even singing along - if you can reach that high. Taylor is also a Canadian Idol & Mariposa Emerging Artist finalist, accomplished TV voice actor, and collaborator with emerging & platinum-selling talent for music in feature films & TV. Out of love for Taylor’s songwriting, Eddie Kramer (Jimi Hendrix, The Beatles, etc), insisted on co-producing his acclaimed debut studio album.

Jillian Matundan, multi-instrumental singer-songwriter, trade unionist, and first-generation Filipina American has delighted audiences with her resonant vocals, acute and relatable observations matched with her unique guitar-style and sense of humor. Singing to the Moon, her first full-length album, debuted at No. 6 on the FAI Folk Chart in March 2024.

View Event →

Night Coast

spotify | youtube

We are Night Coast: your soundtrack to journeys both real and imagined. Inspired by the diverse culture of our hometown, Queens NY, we serve up a sonic current of alt-rock and ambient pop that transports audiences from the confines of the everyday to a place of infinite possibilities. Building on the foundation of iconic artists like Incubus, Linkin Park, and Audioslave, we infuse the familiar with the experimental for a sound that’s simultaneously nostalgic and of-the-moment.

View Event →

Ryan Flynn

spotify | youtube | instagram

ryan flynn, based out of Rochester, New York, are a duo who have carved their niche in the local music scene with their unique blend of heavy synth pop. With a magnetic stage presence and an unmistakable sound, their music is characterized by infectious melodies, pulsating beats, and ethereal synth textures. Their audiences are guided through their performances with the mystical glow of Orb, creating an otherworldly experience in a sonic landscape.

View Event →

Soe Time

I'm Soe Time, a local singer/songwriter from NYC. My style of music can be categorized from blues rock to Latin jazz. I've been performing consistently since 2015. I'm in the process of recording an album. I keep my music upbeat, rhythmic, short & sweet. I enjoy playing mash-ups by transitioning between 3 & 4 songs. I keep my beats spontaneous & unexpected. My all time favorite artist is Queen.

View Event →

Dirty Mother String Band

instagram | facebook

The Dirty Mother String Band are a fine group of musicians who met at jam sessions around Brooklyn. They discovered their shared love of bawdy early blues, jazz and string band music. Liz Rabson (Uke, Harmonica) is the daughter of acclaimed blues woman Ann Rabson, from Virginia but has lived in Brooklyn for twenty-seven years. She is a multi-instrumentalist, these days primarily playing the ukulele. She performs with various local bands, co-organizes the Brooklyn Ukes jam and teaches ukulele at the Jalopy Theatre School of Music. She is the music organizer at the Gowanus Dredgers Canoe Club Boathouse and is active in the Brooklyn folk and roots music scene. Sarah Gancher (Fiddle) is a playwright and fiddle player who grew up playing early jazz in Oakland, California. Sarah Klein (Upright Bass) is an avid knitter, aspiring gardener, and upright bass player. Originally from Florida, she's currently based in Brooklyn, where she hopes to one day find a parking spot. Alex Deane (Guitar) originally hails from Nashville where she developed a love for acoustic music and singing with dear friends. You can find her singing and playing guitar or fiddle at jams and living rooms around Brooklyn.

View Event →

The Sentimentals

website

The Sentimentals (Gene Yellin, Phyllis Elkind, and Sam Dallas) bring heartful harmonies to a hot mix of bluegrass and country. Gene Yellin is a 40 year veteran of the New York bluegrass scene and considered one its best bluegrass singers. He currently plays with Andy Statman in Andy’s Ramble. Phyllis Elkind was the founder of Freddi & the Drumsticks, an all-female rock band, featured in stories on NBC and CBS. She has taught harmony at Jalopy music school for ten years. Sam Dallas is a Brooklyn-based bassist and vocalist. You can find her playing in bands that include Country City, Wifetime, and Paper Anniversary, along with many jams around town! The Sentimentals have featured a stellar list of guest artists in the past – Andy Statman, Charlie Giordano, Kenny Kosek, Trip Henderson.

View Event →

Wiser Time

website | instagram | facebook | youtube | soundcloud

Carmen Sclafani, professionally known as Wiser Time, is a vocalist, songwriter, guitarist and producer from New Jersey/New York, USA. His work has received recognition for it’s soulful vocals and musical style which consists primarily of concept albums that blend rock, Americana, blues and folk influences, and whos third album, "Beggars And Thieves," reached #46 on the Americana Music Charts. Wiser Time recently released the single, “Hanging Around,” from the coming “All Fired Up,” EP in August 2024.

View Event →

J. Roger Davis

website | spotify | instagram

J. Roger Davis -is an American Contemporary Soul singer/songwriter. His early works are influenced by his Appalachia upbringing like family gatherings with homemade Southern food, sweet tea and storytelling. His soulful melodies and acoustics are like wild flowers in a field while his lyrics speak to matters of the heart and daily struggles in life, love and loss. J. Roger Davis Music instills hope for a brighter future and represents inclusion and equality for all people.

View Event →

STRAWBERRY JAM

Instagram

Strawberry Jam is an improvised open jam hosted by Jazz Fusion band Strawberry Sun. The jam is open to all vocalists, guitarists, bassists, keyboardists, drummers, etc, just bring your own instrument! The jam will focus heavily on improvised grooves, and combine elements of jazz, funk, rock, hip hop and R&B,

View Event →

Ruby Rae

linktr.ee

Nashville based Ruby Rae writes and performs music that defies easy categorization: a catalog of influences would include Lori McKenna, Wanda Jackson, and Mazzy Star. Simultaneously catchy and psychological, the sound is cinematic and complex, drawing on diverse sources that include film, mythology, and autobiography. Ruby Rae recently collaborated on a brand new cosmic American record with Producer Lawson White titled True Crime, released fall 2022, and is currently releasing Misdemeanor remixes with various producers.

View Event →

STRAWBERRY JAM

Instagram

Strawberry Jam is an improvised open jam hosted by Jazz Fusion band Strawberry Sun. The jam is open to all vocalists, guitarists, bassists, keyboardists, drummers, etc, just bring your own instrument! The jam will focus heavily on improvised grooves, and combine elements of jazz, funk, rock, hip hop and R&B,

View Event →

Ricky Stein

website | instagram | youtube

Austin-born, New York-based musician Ricky Stein writes songs that seek spiritual common ground between the mesas of West Texas and the cobblestones of South Brooklyn. Song titles such as "American Dreaming," "The Night Is Young," and "Street Lights" depict city life in the modern era. "The Tex-Mex Song" balances out the set with good-natured humor. All songs are delivered with Stein's earnest baritone, accompanied by acoustic guitar, harmonica, and an affable stage presence.

View Event →

Jane Fonda Fan Club

Linktr.ee

The Jane Fonda Fan Club is an Indie Jam Band hailing from Brooklyn, New York. Their unique sound combines elements of classic rock, funk, and psychedelia to create an immersive and energetic experience where they bring both original and classic songs to life through an electrifying performance that will leave you wanting more.

View Event →

UR SO

instagram | tiktok | spotify

UR SO is a alternative/pop band from the suburbs of NYC. Their songs have catchy sing-along choruses and lyrics laced with contemporary wit and observations. UR SO is very much a live band, bringing the audience into the show and making them feel part of the band themselves. UR SO is singer/songwriter Django Santalis, drummer Jacob Falk, guitarist Vincent Lombardi, and Keyboardist Jadyn Castagna.

View Event →

Apollo Flowerchild

linktr.ee

Apollo Flowerchild is an NYC-based singer-songwriter multi-instrumentalist who isn’t married to any single genre. Since starting their musical journey 8 years ago they have managed to sing on Broadway, be recognized by billboard among other publications, and perform all across NYC music venues including but not limited to The Mercury Lounge, Heaven can wait, Rockwood Music hall, 3 Dollar Bill and Purgatory. Apollos voice Carries a sense of soulful light and beauty and is pushed even further by thoughtful, earnest and wacky lyricism. She considers big questions about how a person ought to be in the world, but she conducts her case studies on the most intimate of stages. Jessica Vines

website | instagram

“I like the way that we kiss in the morning. I like the way you look with sun in your eyes.” If the opening lyric to Jessica Vines’ fan favorite “Sun in Your Eyes” captures the excitement and intimacy of young love, it’s just as much a testament to Vines’ blossoming career in bright Los Angeles. Often earning comparisons to Amy Winehouse and Sir Woman, Jessica Vines draws inspiration from Lake Street Dive, Dua Lipa and Olivia Dean. Vines’ vocal performances and effusive lyrics combine determination, sensitivity, attitude, and – refreshingly – an earnest exploration of what it means to be happy. Jessica Vines has been featured on tastemaker 89.3 The Current’s widely acclaimed and internationally streamed radio station. She has also appeared on I’ve Got a Song for That, Rumorcast, LoudMouth Rock Reviews, Prairie Musician’s live in-studio series, JJ Meets World, and North Dakota Today. In expanding on vocal pop, Jessica Vines’ sound incorporates R&B, funk, hip-hop, and rock. Her recordings bring clean, cutting-edge production to an organic ensemble, featuring prominent bass and drums, tasteful guitar, expressive keys, and a command of music theory. Vines’ music leaves the listener excited and hopeful with unique elements that add a refreshing twist on a more nostalgic sound, bridging a classic school of thought with the contemporary. Jessica Vines’ newest single, “For the First Time,” celebrates fresh romance with unabashed optimism and sincerity. You can enjoy “For the First Time,” and others like “Sway” and “Indefinitely,” in your car or headphones – and when you catch Jessica Vines performing in a city near you. Before a crowd, Vines has been lauded for her magnetic presence, expert vocal control, and an accessible sense of humor. Vines champions a rare versatility on stage, shifting smoothly in style and stature from disco diva to sensitive soul singer. As she alerted us in 2023: “I have a story to tell. It’s a very good story.” And fans can’t wait to hear more of it.

Natále

spotify | instagram

An independent genre-defying singer/songwriter who delivers her powerfully visceral songs with a soulful, vintage voice influenced by blues, pop, reggae, and 70s folk rock, Natále provides a unique sonic palette for her listeners to get lost in and find their own. Natále began her career in 2019, a few months prior to the pandemic, releasing her debut single, Day to Night (featuring Patti LaBelle’s trumpet player Matt Cappy) in tandem with a self-directed/produced music video. Six months later, she released her first EP, Giving All to You, mastered by Grammy winning engineer Adam Ayan of Bob Ludwig’s Mastering studios (known for their work with The Rolling Stones, Beyoncé, Madonna, U2, Taylor Swift) while writing new songs during lockdown on a farm in New Hampshire’s white mountains. A year later, after purchasing a forty-foot school bus and traveling the country passing out CDs to radio stations, Natále flew to México City to record her next single, a Spanish reggae song, Moreno, with the help of Latin Grammy nominated legend, Fidel Nadal (Todos Tus Muertos). The two worked closely together, co-producing and writing in Camilo Lara’s recording studio (Mexican Institute of Sound), and released Moreno in 2021, expanding and growing her audiences to Latin America. Inspired by the vibrant culture and artist community, Natále decided to stay in México, where she has been living for the past two and a half years, engaging with local musicians and exchanging ideas. In February 2022, she recorded her latest single, Do You Believe It?, with members of the Mexican reggae band Antidoping, and received support and guidance from the legendary two-time Grammy winning engineer Errol Brown (Bob Marley & The Wailers, Ziggy Marley, Steel Pulse, Shaggy). Currently, Natále is focusing on songwriting and recording, for her upcoming album release - including a collaboration with Grammy winning producer, Austen Jux-Chandler (Adele, Kali Uchis, Ed Sheeran, Lady Gaga) - while also writing for TV and film, including the number one hit Netflix series in Colombia - “La Primera Vez” and a feature film to be released in theaters in México this November. Natále continues to perform live with her band, playing festivals alongside legendary artists such as The Jacksons, The Gipsy Kings, UB40, The Village People, and Buena Vista All Stars.

Dillon Havins

instagram | website

Dillon Havins grew up on a small farm in Dripping Springs, Texas, and started performing gigs across Texas at the age of ten. Eventually, his dedication led him to Boston’s Berklee College of Music, where he expanded his musical horizons. The pandemic brought him back to Texas, where he became the lead guitarist for Sneaky Peaches & the Fuzz. The band played for crowds of over 10,000 people, opened for major touring acts, and garnered over 3 million streams on Spotify. Since 2021, Dillon has worked as a full time musician, playing nearly 1000 gigs at bars, wineries, and restaurants. During this time, he began creating home recordings inspired by his love of nature and a search for peace, which blended together the sounds of artists like Bon Iver, Gregory Alan Isakov, and Joni Mitchell. These recordings, initially a side project, soon became his main musical focus. In August 2024, Dillon will release his first single, "You’re Gonna Find It," and embark on his first national tour.

John Colonna

instagram

John Colonna is a virtuosic and lyrical pianist who mixes many influences into a unique and vibrant sound. He studied classical piano as a child and teenager and was seduced by the power and simple beauty of rock music. Soon his interests turned to jazz and he graduated from Berklee College of Music with a degree in Jazz Composition. After performing across the country in a variety of venues and genres, he attended New York University to study with Don Friedman, the late great jazz pianist. Since receiving his Master’s Degree from NYU he has performed with his own group (the John Colonna Quartet), the Blake Fleming Trio, Renaissance Church in Harlem and teaches at Hartwick college. He regularly performs at various venues in New York City such as Club Groove, Tomi Jazz, Cipriani, Rockwood and Hutaoli.
